HEADWORD: Luxuriancy
<hw>Lux*u"ri*an*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
quality of being luxuriant; luxuriance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Flowers grow up in the garden in the greatest
<qex>luxuriancy</qex> and profusion.</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luxuriant</ent>⟦br⟧
